{
  "_comment": "COG-005 seed A/B task set — 20 tasks. Mode A = CHUMP_PERCEPTION_ENABLED=1 (full perception layer extracts entities/risks/constraints/ambiguity, posts to blackboard, nudges trajectory confidence). Mode B = =0 (empty PerceivedInput, no signals). The hypothesis: perception helps on tasks with extractable structure (file paths, quoted strings, risk markers, ambiguity) and is no-op on trivial chat. The 'perception_signals' field on each task documents what perception SHOULD extract — useful for diagnosis when the A/B fails on a task. Expanded to 100 tasks by EVAL-022.",
